<TEXT>
gilbert lesser one of the countrys most 
prolific theatre poster creators and former promotion director of 
life time and money magazines has died of cancer he was 55 
lesser who did posters for shows including equus the 
elephant man frankenstein and mornings at seven died 
at columbiapresbyterian medical centers milstein hospital on 
tuesday said john toland a longtime friend 
eighty of lessers posters were displayed at the louvre in paris 
in the summer of 1987 and the new design museum in london in 
december 1989 the collection included his logo for the manhattan 
disco studio 54 as well as designs for the martha graham and the 
jose limon dance companies 
lesser who lived in manhattan also designed costumes and stage 
sets for threepenny opera zoo story and the american 
dream at the berkshire playhouse 
he was also responsible for several promotional programs for 
charm and mademoiselle magazines and the smithsonian institution 
lesser in 1987 established the gilbert lesser incr inc an 
international group to help organizations create and plan special 
events 
lesser born in baltimore graduated from the maryland institute 
college of art and from johns hopkins university 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

