<DOCNO> AP900829-0003 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the death sentence of robert alton harris 
the man closest to san quentins gas chamber was upheld wednesday 
by a federal appeals court 
harris now 37 was convicted of the july 1978 murders of two 
san diego teenagers whose car he used in a 3000 bank robbery he 
sought a new penalty trial on the grounds that the psychiatrists 
who assisted his trial lawyer were incompetent for allegedly 
failing to detect a longstanding brain disorder 
judge john noonan of the 9th us circuit court of appeals 
stayed harris execution march 30 four days before he was to die 
he said harris may be entitled to a hearing to determine if his 
constitutional rights were violated 
but over noonans dissent the appeals court ruled 21 wednesday 
that harris claims were meritless 
the majority ruled in the prosecutions favor on every disputed 
issue at least two of which are important for future cases 
the justices said courts arent required to evaluate the 
competence of a defense psychiatrists performance and they said a 
defendant such as harris whose first round of appeals was rejected 
before the us supreme court established the right to psychiatric 
assistance in 1985 cannot even raise the issue under federal law 
a judicial evaluation of a psychiatrists opinion or advice is 
not essential to the accuracy and fairness of the criminal 
process and if applied to past trials would frustrate the 
legitimate goals of the criminal justice system said the opinion 
by judge melvin brunetti 
harris cannot now obtain a second bite at the apple because 
he believes a new group of psychiatrists would offer a different 
defense the opinion said 
defense lawyers can ask for reconsideration by an 11judge panel 
of the court a procedure the court has used several times recently 
in capital cases from other states it can be authorized by a 
majority vote of the courts 27 active judges 
after that harris only remaining appeal is to the us supreme 
court which has ruled against him four times in the past no new 
execution date has been set 
out of 286 prisoners on californias death row harris case is 
the only one to advance beyond the first stage in federal court 
review which commonly lasts several years no one has been 
executed in california since 1967 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

