<TEXT>
daniel m jones was buried with full 
military honors wednesday as friends and family grieved for the 
second member of the armed forces to die since the persian gulf 
crisis began 
jones joined the navy after graduating from high school in 1988 
because he wanted money for college to serve his country and 
most of all to have everybody be proud of him said christina 
russell a friend 
nearly 300 mourners attended morning services at the first 
baptist church in wakefield about 13 miles north of boston 
after a 21gun salute the body of jones an electricians mate 
was buried in nearby forest glade cemetery 
leith a and arlene jones were too overcome with emotion at the 
gravesite to accept the american flag taken from the casket of 
their 19yearold son jones clung to his sobbing wife while 
another mourner accepted the flag for the family which includes 
jones four brothers and two sisters 
jones was electrocuted aug 21 aboard the uss antietam while 
performing routine maintenance on the ships ventilation system 
the ship had been sent to the persian gulf as part of operation 
desert shield which was deployed to counter iraqs aug 2 invasion 
of kuwait 
</TEXT>
