<TEXT>
a solar collector has produced a tiny beam of 
sunlight that outshines the sun its 15 percent brighter than the 
glow at the suns surface 
in a brief note in thursdays journal nature dave cooke and 
colleagues at the university of chicago said they used a sapphire 
light funnel to produce sunlight 84000 times as bright as the 
sunlight striking the earth 
the researchers having beaten the sun at its own game boasted 
that they had done more than set a world record they produced the 
highest concentration of sunlight in the solar system 
two years ago the group reported that it had produced sunlight 
56000 times as concentrated as sunlight at the earths surface 
the concentrator uses a parabolic mirror like those used in 
reflecting telescopes and a nonimaging concentrator made of 
sapphire the mirror reflects light to the broad end of the 
coneshaped concentrator which acts like a funnel the researchers 
said 
light is directed inside the concentrator to emerge in 
concentrated form at the tip of the cone the researchers said 
the bright beam of concentrated sunlight emerged from a 
1millimeter aperture at the tip of the concentrator one 
millimeter is about onetwentyfourth of an inch 
refinements of the technique could lead to the development of a 
laser fired by 
a0568 0443 1240 0829 ra amultrasound 
a0569 0262 1242 0829 ri ampakistan 
