a proposal to declare crack cocaine houses health 
hazards has been dropped and a regulation requiring health and 
safety plans for them has been repealed by the king county health 
board 
after nine months of grappling with the issue the panel voted 
21 tuesday to leave enforcement of cocaine and other drug laws to 
police 
