council said anticrack regulations put the health department in 
this law enforcement role i believe inappropriately 
he said health inspectors lack the training experience and 
temperament to do police work 
the regulation requiring crack house health plans was proposed 
in december it was adopted jan 3 shortly before a change in 
board membership and took effect july 1 
but it never was enforced largely because of concern that it 
gave the appearance of sanctioning illegal drug operations 
prosecutors drafted extensive amendments to establish a civil 
process for declaring premises where crack cocaine is made sold or 
used to be health hazards the declaration made owners and 
operators subject to heavy fines closure and potential loss of the 
property 
