not knowing whats going to happen and being unwilling to make 
decisions he asked 
economist richards suggested that because capital is 
energyintensive the oil price shock points to some scaling back 
of investment spending 
negative contributors were faster business delivery times a 
decline in the money supply a drop in manufacturers unfilled 
orders a shorter average work week a drop in building permits an 
