identified by name said all vehicles trying to enter the city 
would be turned away unless they had permits from local 
authorities he said this was to prevent more armenian national 
army units from reaching the city 
he also said azerbaijanis had shut off the only natural gas 
pipeline to yerevan leaving most of the citys 12 million 
residents without cooking fuel 
the state of emergency in armenia is different in key respects 
from one declared in azerbaijan on jan 15 in azerbaijan soviet 
authorities imposed the emergency after gangs in the capital baku 
attacked armenians and 25 people were reported killed 
it has been lifted throughout the republic except in baku and 
along the armenian border 
armenias parliament passed a declaration of independence last 
week becoming the fifth soviet republic to vote to sever from the 
central soviet state armenia which borders turkey and iran has 
33 million people 
the independence declaration calls for creation of armenias own 
armed forces to safeguard the border which last week was the scene 
of violent conflict with azerbaijanis the declaration also calls 
for nagornokarabakh to become part of armenia 
