said a review of nine studies and a gao analysis found students in 
grades 10 through 12 knew little about federal financial aid 
generally the studies showed parents had little idea of about 
college costs most parents greatly overestimated costs or offered 
unrealistically low estimates ranging from a low of 2000 to a 
high of 60000 a year 
the college board said total available student aid in 198990 
amounted to 279 billion after adjusting for inflation total aid 
increased 10 percent over the 198081 level 
in 1980 only 12 percent of all high school sophomores thought 
the pell grant program was available in their schools and only 8 
percent believed stafford loans a governmentbacked program were 
available 
pell grants the largest aid program are available to all who 
qualify but a 1988 study by the council for advancement and 
support of education found 49 percent of the high school students 
polled incorrectly thought they were ineligible for aid to attend 
an expensive private school if their parents could afford a state 
school 
onethird of those polled also incorrectly believed financial 
