universities found that 59 percent of ninth graders reported 
receiving no information about financial aid from their schools 
the gao report also found that high school students 
knowledgeable about financial aid were more likely to enroll in 
college than students less familiar with such aid 
it seems likely that lack of knowledge and misconceptions 
limit students and parents understanding of postsecondary 
options at worst such ignorance may lead to specific decisions 
about high school courses that close the doors on some future job 
and school possibilities the gao said 
