president mikhail s gorbachev met with his chief 
rival boris n yeltsin for several hours on wednesday and they 
discussed their nations crumbling economy and relations with 
japan a spokesman said 
the meeting was the first between the two since they clashed 
earlier this month over the attempt by russia the soviet unions 
largest republic to seize control over its vast natural resources 
from the central soviet government 
yeltsin is president of the russian republic gorbachev issued a 
presidential decree last week nullifying the russian move 
this was a very good and a very constructive discussion 
said gorbachevs new spokesman vitaly ignatenko 
ignatenko said the two talked about matters relating to russia 
the entire soviet union and international topics including europe 
and relations with japan 
he provided few details on the discussion but he said the 
soviet economy was a central theme 
the situation in the country is such that we are on the 
threshold of major decisions ignatenko said we have 
approached such a decisive stage when we are speaking about a real 
change in economic structures and new relationships within the 
union itself 
old structures are becoming a thing of the past but the new 
structures are still emerging this gives rise to a certain 
instability to heated discussions and this situation cannot easily 
be kept under control 
gorbachev and yeltsin have jointly appointed a commission to 
study making the transition to a market economy another 
commission led by soviet prime minister nikolai ryzhkov is also 
drafting plans for the economic switch 
gorbachev favors a gradual approach to avoid the shock of sudden 
price increases yeltsin wants to make the transition quickly 
arguing that the ailing economy needs urgent measures 
yeltsin has accused ryzhkov of duplicating his work and said if 
more than one plan were presented to the national parliament the 
russian republic would go its own way 
ignatenko said gorbachev would convene a joint meeting of his 
presidential council and the council of the federation on thursday 
gorbachev has invited yeltsin and other leaders of the soviet 
republics and autonomous regions to attend 
this meeting also will focus on the economy and the unrest in 
the republics ignatenko said 
today our leadership is expressing only one wish to stabilize 
the situation to protect the new economic policy by exercising its 
powers to defend perestroika he said the coming few months 
should be decisive in many ways 
