<TEXT>
a law has been drafted to open the first 
stock exchange in postwar poland a government spokesman said 
wednesday 
the law on securities and the stock market represents the next 
step in polands legislative drive toward introducing capitalism 
last month the parliament passed a statute on selling stateowned 
industries to private owners 
jan buchacz a spokesman for the government committee 
established to reform polands laws on ownership said the draft 
law on the stock exchange is ready for public discussion 
we want everyone to add his opinion and see if there is no 
essential discrepancy in it he said 
he said the law could be passed by parliament within the next 
few weeks 
creation of the stock exchange is fundamental to polands 
economic reform program which is aimed at transforming the 
centralized economy to a marketdriven system under the 
privatization law all citizens are to be given bonds which can be 
exchanged for stock in the previously stateowned companies 
the draft law provides a legal framework for the functioning of 
the stock market establishing a statecontrolled stock exchange 
and a committee to grant licenses for issuing and selling shares 
the government daily rzeczpospolita reported wednesday 
i treat it as a continuation of the privatization law 
another push another expression of that law buchacz told the 
associated press 
the government committee studied international stock markets and 
followed various solutions and experiences especially of the 
british and american systems buchacz said 
but we also watched closely what was happening in hungary 
he said referring to the first stock exchange in the east bloc 
which opened in budapest on june 21 
rzeczpospolita observed that implementation of the stock 
exchange law will mean creation of a new professional group 
brokers who will receive licenses from the stock committee and 
will be expected to form an association 
buchacz said his committee is preparing training programs and 
examinations for brokers a profession virtually unknown in poland 
and hopes that the first brokers will receive licenses in october 
or november 
after this law is passed we will need only a lot of wise 
heads he added 
poland had a stock exchange until 1939 when nazi germany 
invaded the sovietbacked communists who consolidated power after 
world war ii did not reopen it 
