<TEXT>
edmund north the oscarwinning 
coauthor of patton and a lifelong crusader for the writers 
guild of america has died from complications following surgery he 
was 79 
north died tuesday at st johns hospital and health center 
said guild spokeswoman cheryl rhoden 
with james gow north wrote his first movie one night of 
love starring grace moore at the age of 21 it was voted one of 
the bestwritten films of the year by the newly former screen 
writers guild a union with which north would have a productive 
relationship 
in a career spanning 60 years his credits included the day 
the earth stood still sink the bismarck cowboy young 
man with a horn and damn the defiant 
born in new york city to stage performers robert north and 
stella maury norths first writing jobs were at fox and rko his 
early films were i dream too much with henry fonda and lucille 
ball all the kings horses murder on a bridle path 
bunker bean and im still alive 
he served in the signal corps in world war ii 
upon his return to hollywood north was president of the guilds 
screen branch president of the pension fund and frequently 
chairman of the contract negotiating committee in all he served 
on more than 40 guild committees 
for many of us eddie was the guild the most beloved of all 
our members said david rintels a former president of the wga 
west he was the fairestminded man i ever met a man of great 
oldfashioned virtues 
norths other film credits include dishonored lady 
flamingo road dialogue only colorado territory in a 
lonely place only the valiant the outcasts of poker 
flat destry the far horizons the proud ones and 
the fiercest heart 
in 1982 north wrote and produced race to oblivion an 
antiwar film made for physicians for social responsibility he 
also served on the board for the national captioning institute a 
group created in 1979 to provide closed captioning for television 
programs 
north cowrote 1970s patton with francis ford coppola 
starring george c scott as the flamboyant world war ii general 
the film won oscars for best picture best actor for scott best 
director for franklin schaffner and best script 
north is survived by his wife collette daughters bobbie and 
susan and two grandchildren 
a memorial service is pending 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

