the killings of five people in 
gainesville this week evoked memories of another florida campus 
nightmare the fatal bludgeoning of two sorority sisters by serial 
killer ted bundy 12 years ago 
everybody knows that it happened here kim ewing a 
sophomore at florida state university said tuesday its kind of 
the first thing you associate with killings like this 
this weeks killings occurred near the university of florida 
campus about 2 hours to the southeast 
a chill swept through the state capital when margaret bowman and 
lisa levy were found slain on jan 15 1978 at the chi omega 
sorority house three other women students were severely beaten 
with an oak limb 
lt jack handley of the florida state university police 
department who was on the force when it happened said people had 
trouble accepting that such a crime happened in quiet tallahassee 
if youre looking for one way to describe it i would say it 
was total disbelief handley said these things just are not 
supposed to happen in a college community 
bundy was executed in floridas electric chair jan 24 1989 
for the february 1978 killing of 12yearold kimberly leach who 
was abducted in lake city about a month after the chi omega murders 
crowds cheered outside the florida state prison when the switch 
was thrown 
bundy also received the death penalty for the sorority slayings 
and authorities believe he was responsible for three dozen other 
killings across the country 
diane cossin now an executive assistant to us attorney dexter 
lehtinen in miami was a member of chi omega and was awakened by 
the sounds of her two friends being killed she comforted one of 
the victims before she died and later was a witness at bundys 
trial 
what i remember was an enormous feeling of loss of the 
shattering of the safety you felt it was like being in a crisis 
she said fear is elevated a great amount of anxiety was felt by 
everyone 
cossin had to put off law school while the trial was held and 
when she returned she decided to shift her focus from family to 
criminal law when lehtinen was in the florida legislature she 
helped him draft legislation expanding rights of crime victims 
i think it played a big part in what i do now you can either 
avoid something or you can get in there and try to do something 
about it she said 
