<TEXT>
magellans mission to map venus has been 
delayed again until late september while nasa tries to figure out 
why the spacecraft keeps losing touch with earth 
have patience with us were going to make it work tony 
spear magellan project manager at the space agencys jet 
propulsion laboratory said tuesday 
magellans radio link to earth failed for 14 hours starting aug 
16 and for 17 hours beginning aug 21 while the craft was in 
orbit around venus 
spear said he organized a team of 40 engineers from the lab and 
from martin marietta corp which built magellan in denver to 
determine what is wrong with the spacecraft and fix it 
before magellan started malfunctioning nasa planned for it to 
make pictures and maps of venus on a regular basis starting 
saturday last week spear said engineers hoped to have magellan 
working properly by midseptember 
now he said were targeting for the last week in september 
to start mapping 
mapping is being delayed not only to fix magellan but also 
because the crafts troubles have left engineers mentally and 
physically exhausted spear said weve decided to give the 
team three days off around labor day 
magellans 744 million mission is to use radar to peer through 
venus thick clouds and make the best pictures and maps yet of the 
planets surface the spacecraft was launched from space shuttle 
atlantis in may 1989 
pictures made during an aug 16 test showed quake faults vast 
solidified lava flows cinder cones a lavafilled meteorite impact 
crater and countless valleys and mountain ridges on earths nearest 
planetary neighbor 
magellan functioned almost flawlessly during the 15 months it 
traveled a looping 948millionmile route to venus one major 
theory is that something went wrong when the craft went into orbit 
around venus on aug 10 spear said 
nasa also has been troubled by the temporary grounding of the 
shuttle fleet and a focusing flaw on the hubble space telescope 
spear said engineeers will try to determine if previously 
unknown electrical fields or particles around venus are disrupting 
magellans electronics 
the engineers will also examine a computer that ran amok during 
the communications failures and look at changes in magellan as it 
went into orbit including the possibility of short circuits 
spear ruled out the possibility raised friday that magellans 
braking rocket may have failed to separate from the spacecraft 
after it went into orbit 
</TEXT>
