will be called the macintosh lc the color monitor will be made by 
sony corp 
the lc is expected to have a list price of 2800 compared with 
4669 for the current cheapest color mac 
the lc also will have room for a chip board that apple will 
introduce to allow the machine to run software designed for the 
apple ii computer which can be found in more than twothirds of 
school classrooms that are equipped with computers 
industry analysts have said apple needs to find a way to allow 
software written for the millions of apple iis to be used on the 
newer macintosh line otherwise apple ii users will be reluctant 
