<TEXT>
a federal appeals court says the resolution 
trust corp can override an arkansas banking law to sell insolvent 
thrifts and their branches to banks an rtc attorney said the 
ruling has nationwide implications 
on tuesday a threejudge panel from the 8th us circuit court 
of appeals ruled 21 to overturn a lower court ruling that the sale 
of independence federal savings bank of batesville to worthen bank 
and trust co of little rock would violate arkansass 
branchbanking law 
that law prohibits banks from having branches outside their home 
counties 
the rtc a government agency created to clean up insolvent 
thrifts argued that it was granted broad rulemaking authority by 
congress in its mission to maximize returns and minimize the losses 
rtc attorney dorothy nichols said the case had nationwide 
implications because 26 states have similar laws 
the rtcs authority to override state laws has been challenged 
in new mexico and colorado rtc spokesman steve katsanos said a 
district court judge in new mexico sided with the rtc earlier this 
year he said 
in colorado a hearing on the case is scheduled sept 5 
katsanos said the district court there has issued a restraining 
order to keep the rtc from going ahead with any transaction that 
would involve overriding colorado state law 
tuesdays appeals court ruling was welcomed by worthen president 
and chairman curt bradbury 
we consider todays ruling to be a significant victory for the 
taxpayers of the united states he said 
we are strongly committed to assisting in the resolution of 
the sampl crisis in arkansas and consider our opportunity to purchase 
independence to be a beneficial stabilizing force for the 
financialservices segment of our economy bradbury said 
the acquisition would bring assets of worthens parent company 
worthen banking corp to 21 million according to a news release 
from worthen that would make it the largest bank holding company 
in the state 
in arguments before the appellate court the rtcs nichols 
argued that most of independences branch offices would be shut 
down by the rtc if the institution were sold piecemeal 
the most valuable assets of sampls in dire straits arent their 
loan portfolios she said the most valuable asset of a failed 
thrift is its branches 
arkansas state bank commissioner bill j ford argued that the 
states 1988 branching law which would permit statewide branches 
gradually over 10 years was necessary to ensure fair competition 
ford and the arkansas independent bankers association had filed 
suit june 28 to block the proposed sale to worthen 
tuesdays opinion overruling a decision by us district judge 
stephen m reasoner of little rock was written by circuit judge 
john r gibson for circuit judge frank j magill 
senior circuit judge gerald w heaney dissented he agreed with 
arkansas officials that the rtcs regulation referred only to the 
ability of the savings associations to operate branches and not to 
the ability of a bank to retain and operate branches 
at issue is an rtc regulation that permits banks making 
emergency acquisitions of insolvent thrifts such as independence to 
operate the branches of the thrift as bank branches independence 
has 20 branches in 15 counties 
