<TEXT>
lockheed corp on wednesday unveiled its 
version of a futuristic fighter proposed for the 21st century as 
air force officials cited the middle east crisis as the need for 
such a craft 
the lockheed yf22 prototype of the advanced tactical fighter 
followed mondays launch of a prototype made by northrop corp the 
two designs are competing for a multibilliondollar contract 
the plane lockheed unveiled at its palmdale manufacturing plant 
was much more compact than the northrop version 
both planes have smooth contours to help them evade radar and 
are built of advanced composite materials the lockheed aircraft 
has stubby wings while the northrop plane is longer with a 
cigarlike fuselage and a wingspan that looks like a kite 
a music system blared wagners flight of the valkyries as 
the lockheed plane was rolled out although unlike its competition 
the yf22 stayed on the ground after its rollout officials would 
not say when it would be flown 
lockheed chairman daniel m tellep said it will not matter that 
northrop got its aircraft up first 
it is not he who flies first it is he who flies best he 
said 
the contract calls for 750 fighter planes for the air force and 
approximately 500 for the navy at a cost of 51 million apiece the 
price tag is about twice the cost of the f15 eagle the current 
frontline fighter deployed in the middle east 
the atf program faced fading prospects for approval in congress 
before iraqs invasion of kuwait on aug 2 but the crisis has 
enhanced prospects for approval of major defense projects 
air force maj gen joseph w ralston said he is optimistic 
about congessional funding for the atf program desspite recent 
defense spending cuts 
in building the yf22 prototype lockheed teamed with the boeing 
corp and general dynamics corp northrop teamed with mcdonnell 
douglas corp for its test version of the futuristic fighter 
the winner must give the pentagon a fighter plane that can fly 
twice the speed of sound is highly maneuverable and uses 
radarevading stealth technology 
if northrop gets the contract atf planes will be built in 
southern california lockheed has said if it wins the competition 
the fighters will be made in marietta ga 
